"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442560","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-13","<p>The number of disputed cases filed but withdrawn by each of the three authorised tenancy deposit schemes in the last five years is set out in the tables below.</p><br /><p><strong>Number of cases withdrawn before adjudication by approved scheme</strong></p><p><br><em> 2010/11(1) 2011/12 2012/13 2013/14 2014/15</em></p><p><strong>MyDeposits (2)</strong></p><p>177 1,012 1,324 1,626 1,728</p><br /><p><em> 2011 2012 2013 2014 2015</em></p><p><br><strong>Deposit Protection Service (3)</strong></p><p>1,049 (4) 1,945 1,888 2,489 2,464</p><p><br><strong>The Dispute Service</strong></p><p>832 1,186 1,810 2,140 2,075</p><br /><p>(1) From 24 November 2010</p><p>(2) Figures include cases where tenants have raised a dispute but scheme has been unable to contact them for further information.</p><p>(3) Figures include cases where (i) both parties have reached agreement (ii) notification given that the case is going to court (iii) one party has not submitted any evidence within the required timescale which has resulted in the disputed amount being paid to the other party and (iv) other reasons.</p><p>(4) From June to December 2011</p><br /><p>The upward trend in the number of cases withdrawn before adjudication is a result of the successful use of mediation services by the schemes before the formal adjudication process begins and the detailed guidance and advice provided to both landlords and tenants by the schemes to help avoid disputes.</p><br />","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-01-13T17:34:27.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442560/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442560/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442560/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-05","Tenancy Deposit Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many disputes have been filed through an accredited tenancy deposit scheme and withdrawn before a final decision was made in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","20905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442561","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-13","<p>The holding costs for the site relate to the entirety of the site and are consistent with the legal and health and safety obligations of the Homes and Communities Agency as land owner.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","20966 ; 20968 ; 20971","2016-01-13T17:23:33.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442561/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442561/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442561/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-05","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many leases of what tenure are planned for the new homes to be built on the direct commissioning sites at (a) Northstowe, (b) Old Oak Common, (c) Daedelus Waterfront, (d) Connaught Barracks and (e) Lower Grayling Well.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","20972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442562","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-13","<p>The Homes and Communities Agency continues to work with the local authority to explore options for bringing forward the wider Daedalus site.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-01-13T11:36:26.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442562/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442562/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442562/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-05","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the announcement of 4 January 2016, The Government will directly build affordable homes, what steps he is taking to catalyse the delivery of the wider commercial development in the direct commissioning site at Daedelus Waterfront.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","20969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442563","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-13","<p>The direct commissioning pilots will follow the normal planning and commercial processes for determining the phasing of homes and associated facilities.</p><br />","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","20964 ; 20967","2016-01-13T11:40:47.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442563/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442563/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442563/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-05","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the announcement of 4 January 2016, The Government will directly build affordable homes, whether the new high street, schools and leisure facilities and commercial and office space are intended to be open at the same time as new homes take their first residents at the direct commissioning site at Old Oak Common.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","20970"
