"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442576","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-01-11","<p>I have received no representations from businesses on this issue.</p><p>This Government supports the system of co-regulation and self-regulation, overseen by the independent Advertising Standards Authority and underpinned by consumer protection legislation. This regulatory system is independent of the Government and is ultimately responsible for setting the standards in advertising, ensuring that all adverts, wherever they appear, are legal, decent, honest and truthful.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-01-11T12:04:49.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442576/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442576/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442576/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-01-05","Business: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what representations he has received from businesses on the enforcement of minor breaches of the Advertising Codes by the Advertising Standards Authority; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Holly Lynch","Halifax","Holly Lynch","21035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442577","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-01-15","<p>The costs reported in the January 2015 National Audit Office Report were based on average direct cabinet costs in September 2014, which were lower than envisaged at the time of the contract. Underspends at the end of the projects will be available for further investment in superfast broadband roll-out.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-01-15T12:37:40.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442577/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442577/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442577/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-01-05","Broadband: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 14 December 2015 to Question 19214 and with reference to Chapter 3 of the National Audit Office Report, entitled The Superfast (Rural) Broadband Programme: update, published in January 2015, for what reason the amount spent per cabinet is approximately double the amount estimated by the National Audit Office.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","20986"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442578","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-01-14","<p>Government are committed to providing the best sporting opportunities for children. DCMS leads the School Games programme which involves the Youth Sport Trust and Sport England working with 38 of the National Governing Bodies of Sports, including the Tennis Foundation, to support schools in delivering competitions for all children. In addition, our Sports Strategy, published in December 2015, has enabled Sport England to fund sport for children from the age of 5 onwards.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2016-01-14T11:50:58.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442578/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442578/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442578/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-01-05","Tennis: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what funding his Department provides to promote tennis for children under 10 years.","false","Biography information for Oliver Colvile","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Oliver Colvile","20923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442579","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-01-15","<p>The UK mobile network operators (Vodafone, Three, O2 and EE, together with Virgin Mobile) have signed a Code of Practice on Consumer Billing, which sets out a number of ways help customers to avoid excess charges when exceeding their monthly allowance. The code outlines the need for regular updates on usage, so customers can manage spend. For example, operators committed to sending alerts to customers - usually SMS messages - when they are nearing their bundle limits.</p><p>In addition, for contracts entered into after 23 January 2014, consumers can exit contracts without penalty, and hence can switch to another provider or tariff, when the agreed core price (usually the monthly subscription) increases. All communications providers have to comply with these rules when increasing prices.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-01-15T11:45:10.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442579/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442579/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442579/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-01-05","Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what his Department's policy is on capping exceed costs on mobile phone contracts for consumers.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","20904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442580","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-01-11","<p>Tickets to the Commemorative Event at the Thiepval Memorial were allocated in pairs to residents of the UK via a random ballot, which gave no weighting to residents of a particular area of the UK.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","20930","2016-01-11T17:31:37.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442580/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442580/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442580/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-01-05","World War I: Anniversaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of tickets for the Thiepval Memorial event on 1 July 2016 have been allocated to applicants from (a) England, (b) Scotland, (c) Wales and (d) Northern Ireland; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","20929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442581","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-01-11","<p>Tickets to the Commemorative Event at the Thiepval Memorial were allocated in pairs to residents of the UK via a random ballot, which gave no weighting to residents of a particular area of the UK.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","20929","2016-01-11T17:31:37.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442581/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442581/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442581/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-01-05","World War I: Anniversaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many tickets to the Thiepval Memorial event on 1 July 2016 have been allocated to applicants from (a) England, (b) Scotland, (c) Wales and (d) Northern Ireland; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","20930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442582","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-01-11","Applicants were required to submit details online, or via a postal form, between 28 September and 18 November 2015. Once the ballot closed, a computer system randomly selected the successful applicants by their reference numbers - so that no weighting was added to any other factor such as geographic location or date of application.<p>The ballot was administered by an external company, SEE Tickets, with previous experience of the managing ticketing and ballots for large scale events. No additional observers were involved in the draw process.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2016-01-11T17:48:45.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442582/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442582/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442582/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-01-05","World War I: Anniversaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what process was used for administering the ballot for tickets to the Thiepval Memorial event on 1 July 2016; whether observers were appointed to scrutinise that process; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","20931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442583","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-11","<p>We do not comment on intelligence matters I am therefore withholding the information as its disclosure would or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or Security of the Armed Forces.</p><br />","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-01-11T15:15:09.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442583/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442583/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442583/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-05","Afghanistan: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 11 of the Op HERRICK (Afghanistan) Aircraft Statistics document, published on 29 October 2015, how many of the 68 strikes made using the Dual Mode Brimstone missile during operation HERRICK were completed with the aid of ground-based HUMINT.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","20951"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442584","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-11","<br /><p>No contract has yet been awarded for the Successor primary lighting system.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","20945","2016-01-11T15:14:32.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442584/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442584/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442584/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-05","Trident Submarines: Lighting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what process his Department followed in awarding the lighting contracts for the Successor submarines.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","20943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442585","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-11","<p>All Ministry of Defence programmes are routinely subject to regular review as part of the standard approvals and scrutiny process. The most recent review of the Successor programme was produced in December 2015.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-01-11T15:13:45.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442585/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442585/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442585/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-05","Trident Submarines: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when his Department conducted its most recent review of the procurement process for the Successor submarines.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","20944"
