"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442358","Department of Health","false","2016-01-07","<p>This information is not available in the format requested.</p><br /><p>Official statistics for NHS trusts in England are published by NHS England on the number of patients delayed on the last Thursday of each month and the total delayed days during the month for all patients delayed throughout the month. The latest publication of this data was for delays occurring in October 2015 and was published on 10 December 2015.</p><br /><p>It is not possible to calculate a montly average or the longest waits from these data. Health is a devolved matter in Wales.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","20854 ; 20855 ; 20857 ; 20858","2016-01-07T11:43:48.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442358/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442358/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442358/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-04","Hospital Beds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the average time was between a patient being declared fit to leave hospital and being discharged in (a) England and Wales, (b) London and (c) each health trust in London in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","20856"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442359","Department of Health","false","2016-01-07","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has recently consulted stakeholders on the suitability of Lutetium-177 Dotatate - a type of peptide receptor radionuclide therapy (PRRT) - for treating unresectable, somatostatin receptor-positive gastroentero-pancreatic neuroendocrine tumours without disease progression for referral to its technology appraisal work programme. A decision on its referral to NICE will be taken shortly.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-01-07T11:33:37.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442359/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442359/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/442359/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-04","Pancreatic Cancer: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when his Department plans to make a decision on whether to refer for consideration by NICE PRRNT treatment for pancreatic cancers.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","20840"
