","HL4807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439755","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-08","<p>65+ GGB “Pensioner” Bonds were a special issue aimed at helping pensioners who rely on their savings in retirement. There are currently no plans for a further issue.</p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2016-01-08T14:02:35.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439755/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439755/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439755/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-22","National Savings Bonds: Pensioners","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they will clarify whether they intend to reissue the 65+ Guarantee of Growth Bonds as and when they mature.","false","Biography information for Lord Trefgarne",,"Lord Trefgarne","HL4808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439756","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-01-08","<p>Whilst the specific information requested is not held, the Ministry of Justice recently published statistics on child dependents of female offenders, which can be found at gov.uk on the <em>Statistics at MOJ</em> pages under the topic <em>Ad-hoc justice statistics</em>. A copy of the report is attached here.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2016-01-08T14:04:25.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439756/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439756/answer","female-offenders-child-dependents-statistics.pdf","female-offenders-child-dependents-statistics.pdf","Female offenders, dependent child stats","Female offenders, dependent child stats","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439756/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-12-22","Prison Sentences: Females","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Faulks on 17 December (HL4250), whether they now have any additional information about the number of women responsible for one or more young children who are currently serving prison sentences in England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Lord Trefgarne",,"Lord Trefgarne","HL4809"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439757","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-07","<p>There are no checks in place to ensure that local authorities comply with the Local Authorities’ Traffic Orders (Procedure) (England and Wales) Regulations 1996, including the duty concerning consultation. Anyone can complain if they consider that the authority has failed to comply with their duty. Complaints should initially be raised with the authority concerned, and if they are not satisfactorily addressed, they can be raised with the Local Government Ombudsman. Alternatively, failure to comply with the consultation requirements in regulation 6 would be grounds for bringing a legal challenge against an order under paragraph 35 of Schedule 9 to the Road Traffic Regulation Act 1984.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-01-07T12:39:48.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439757/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439757/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439757/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-12-22","Road Traffic Control","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon on 14 December (HL4061), what checks are in place to ensure that Regulation 6 of the Local Authorities' Traffic Orders (Procedure) (England and Wales) Regulations 1996 is complied with; who is entitled to complain if that Regulation is not complied with, and to whom; and what penalties are incurred by local authorities or London boroughs for failing to comply with that regulation.","false","Biography information for Baroness Wolf of Dulwich",,"Baroness Wolf of Dulwich","HL4810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439758","Department of Health","false","2016-01-06","<p>NHS England is undertaking a programme of work to engage, inform and support commissioners, clinicians, pharmacists, patients and others in their consideration of the optimal use of biosimilar medicines. In September 2015 they published a <em>What is a Biosimilar Medicine?</em> guide, which provides an update for clinical and non-clinical stakeholders about the developing role of biosimilar medicines in the NHS in England and to support the safe, effective and consistent use of all biological medicines, including biosimilar medicines, to the benefit of patients. A copy is attached and is also available at:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/biosimilar-guide.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/biosimilar-guide.pdf</a></p><br /><p>NHS England has also convened a National Biosimilar Medicines Group, chaired by the Chief Pharmaceutical Officer, whose role includes improving education and understanding of both the theory and practical considerations related to biosimilar medicines.</p><br /><p>Guidance to prescribers requires them to explain to patients the likely benefits, risks and burdens, including serious and common side effects of treatments they are proposing. The <em>What is a Biosimilar Medicine?</em> guide makes it clear that patients’ needs preferences and values are an essential part of evidence based medicine. Local collaborations involving both patients and clinicians have been successful in introducing biosimilars.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL4812","2016-01-06T15:04:22.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439758/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439758/answer","HL4811 HL4812 - library document.pdf","HL4811 HL4812 - library document.pdf","What is a biosimilar medicine?","What is a biosimilar medicine?","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439758/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-22","Biomedicines","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what work has been undertaken by NHS England to ensure that prescribers and commissioners have the right information to introduce biosimilar medicines in a safe and sustainable way.","false","Biography information for Baroness Brinton",,"Baroness Brinton","HL4811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439759","Department of Health","false","2016-01-06","<p>NHS England is undertaking a programme of work to engage, inform and support commissioners, clinicians, pharmacists, patients and others in their consideration of the optimal use of biosimilar medicines. In September 2015 they published a <em>What is a Biosimilar Medicine?</em> guide, which provides an update for clinical and non-clinical stakeholders about the developing role of biosimilar medicines in the NHS in England and to support the safe, effective and consistent use of all biological medicines, including biosimilar medicines, to the benefit of patients. A copy is attached and is also available at:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/biosimilar-guide.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/biosimilar-guide.pdf</a></p><br /><p>NHS England has also convened a National Biosimilar Medicines Group, chaired by the Chief Pharmaceutical Officer, whose role includes improving education and understanding of both the theory and practical considerations related to biosimilar medicines.</p><br /><p>Guidance to prescribers requires them to explain to patients the likely benefits, risks and burdens, including serious and common side effects of treatments they are proposing. The <em>What is a Biosimilar Medicine?</em> guide makes it clear that patients’ needs preferences and values are an essential part of evidence based medicine. Local collaborations involving both patients and clinicians have been successful in introducing biosimilars.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL4811","2016-01-06T15:04:28.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439759/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439759/answer","HL4811 HL4812 - library document.pdf","HL4811 HL4812 - library document.pdf","What is a biosimilar medicine?","What is a biosimilar medicine?","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439759/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-22","Biomedicines","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what provisions have been put in place by NHS England to ensure that patients who are being prescribed biosimilar medicines are informed about the medicines and have given their consent.","false","Biography information for Baroness Brinton",,"Baroness Brinton","HL4812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439760","Department of Health","false","2016-01-05","<p>In 2008, the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA) issued best practice guidance on the prescribing of biological products. This advised:</p><br /><p>“All biosimilar products are prescription only medicines (POM). When prescribing biological products, it is good practice to use the brand name. This will ensure that automatic substitution of a biosimilar product does not occur when the medicine is dispensed by the pharmacist. Products (biosimilar and reference) that have the same international non-proprietary name (INN) are not to be presumed identical for the reasons given above.”</p><br /><p>The MHRA does not have responsibility for monitoring the compliance of healthcare professionals with its prescribing guidance. The responsibility for prescribing rests with the practitioner who has clinical responsibility for their patient's care and we would expect practitioners to take any relevant guidance into account when making their prescribing decisions. Practitioner professional bodies also have a role in setting out best practice to their members.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-01-05T10:12:27.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439760/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439760/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439760/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-22","Biomedicines","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government which organisation has responsibility for ensuring implementation and compliance with the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency guidance, which states that biologic medicines should be prescribed by brand name and tracked by batch number.","false","Biography information for Baroness Brinton",,"Baroness Brinton","HL4813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439761","Department of Health","false","2016-01-06","<p>The Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency has the responsibility for ensuring compliance with European Union legislation on pharmacovigilance.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-01-06T14:50:55.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439761/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439761/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439761/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-22","Drugs: Safety","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government which organisation has responsibility for ensuring compliance with EU legislation on pharmacovigilance.","false","Biography information for Baroness Brinton",,"Baroness Brinton","HL4814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439762","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-07","<p>The Government is committed to taking action on vehicle emissions testing that restores consumer confidence and delivers our wider air quality and climate objectives. We strongly support the current Real Driving Emissions agreement, which is expected to significantly reduce average real world NOx emissions from new diesel cars from 2017. It makes type approval requirements for diesel vehicles significantly more stringent by requiring manufacturers to ensure real-world emissions are maintained below 2.1 times the laboratory-testing limit in 2017 and at or below the laboratory-testing limit by 2020 (with a margin for measurement uncertainty). Issues relating to vehicle emissions are considered in the context of the UK Government’s plans for air quality. More detail is set out in the air quality plans published by the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs on the 17<sup>th</sup> December.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-01-07T12:42:17.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439762/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439762/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439762/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-12-22","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in making their decision about how to vote on the implementation of real driving emissions tests at the 28 October meeting of the Technical Committee on Motor Vehicles, whether they took into account (1) estimates from DEFRA and Public Health England that pollution from mono-nitrogen oxides is responsible for 23,500 premature deaths in the UK per annum, (2) the 2010 estimates from the WHO suggesting that air-pollution related deaths cost the UK $83,069 per annum, (3) the failure of London, Leeds, and Birmingham to maintain nitrogen dioxide levels within legal limits over the past five years, and (4) the Supreme Court’s ruling in <i>R (on the application of ClientEarth) v Secretary of State for the Environment, Food and Rural Affairs </i>[2015] UKSC 28 on 29 April that they should take immediate action to tackle air pollution.","false","Biography information for Baroness Falkner of Margravine",,"Baroness Falkner of Margravine","HL4815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439763","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-07","<br /><p>The Government is committed to taking action on vehicle emissions testing that restores consumer confidence and delivers our wider air quality and climate objectives. We strongly support the current Real Driving Emissions agreement, which is expected to significantly reduce average real world NOx emissions from new diesel cars from 2017. It makes type approval requirements for diesel vehicles significantly more stringent by requiring manufacturers to ensure real-world emissions are maintained below 2.1 times the laboratory-testing limit in 2017 and at or below the laboratory-testing limit by 2020 (with a margin for measurement uncertainty). Issues relating to vehicle emissions are considered in the context of the UK Government’s plans for air quality. More detail is set out in the air quality plans published by the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs on the 17<sup>th</sup> December.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-01-07T12:38:29.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439763/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439763/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439763/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-12-22","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the failure of London, Leeds, and Birmingham to maintain nitrogen dioxide levels within legal limits over the past five years, what assessment they have made of whether relaxing emissions standards for cars is compatible with public health and legal requirements to control urban pollution.","false","Biography information for Baroness Falkner of Margravine",,"Baroness Falkner of Margravine","HL4816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439764","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-07","<p>The Government did not respond to the findings of the ICCT. This research confirmed the importance of ongoing work by Department for Transport officials on the development of a new European regulation to address issues around real world driving emissions.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-01-07T12:37:35.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439764/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439764/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439764/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-12-22","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what response they made to the October 2014 findings by the International Council on Clean Transportation that some vehicles were producing emissions at seven times the legal limit.","false","Biography information for Baroness Falkner of Margravine",,"Baroness Falkner of Margravine","HL4817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439765","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-08","<p>The Office for National Statistics (ONS) jointly with HM Treasury publish the public sector finances statistical bulletin on a monthly basis, which provides the latest available estimates for key aspects of Public Sector Finances.</p><br /><p>The latest release was published on 22 December covering the November 2015 public sector finances.[1]</p><br /><p>Borrowing for the 8 months to November is £6.6 bn less than the same period last year against an Autumn Statement forecast of a £15.7bn full year fall. It’s clear that there is no shortcut to fixing the public finances. That’s why the Chancellor used the Autumn Statement and Spending Review to set out our plan to finish the job and build a resilient economy.</p><p><br></p><p>The independent Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR) are responsible for producing the forecasts of the public finances. They have published a detailed commentary on 22 December, which assesses the latest estimates included in the bulletin against their latest forecast<sup><sup>[2]</sup></sup>.</p><br /><p><br></p><p>[1] <em><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/public-sector-finances-bulletin" target="_blank"><strong>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/public-sector-finances-bulletin</strong></a></em></p><br /><p>[2] <em><a href="http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/wordpress/docs/Dec-2015-Commentary-on-the-Public-Sector-Finances-release.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/wordpress/docs/Dec-2015-Commentary-on-the-Public-Sector-Finances-release.pdf</strong></a></em></p><br />",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2016-01-08T13:57:00.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439765/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439765/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439765/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-22","Public Finance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the difference between the public finance forecasts for 2015–16 and the actual financial figures available to date, and what assessment have they made of the reasons for the difference.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL4818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439766","Department for Education","false","2016-01-11","<p>Equality Advisory Support Service (EASS) costs are calculated on a per case basis, covering everything from an initial inquiry through to final action on behalf of the customer, but the EASS estimate of the call element of a case is under £10.</p><br /><p>The costs per call or per contact of similar services to EASS are treated as commercially confidential information by the providers concerned.</p><br /><p>The numbers of calls handled by the service each year since 1 October 2012 are provided in the table below.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Contacts via telephone</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct 2012 to Sept 2013</p></td><td><p>37,379</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct 2013 to Sept 2014</p></td><td><p>39,095</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct 2014 to Sept 2015</p></td><td><p>41,032</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct 2015 to Nov 2015</p></td><td><p>7,630</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>125,136</p></td></tr></tbody></table>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2016-01-11T13:18:09.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439766/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439766/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439766/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-22","Equality Advisory and Support Service","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government (1) what is the cost per call of the Equality Advisory Support Service, including the wrap-up time after each call; (2) how this cost compares to benchmarked comparators; and (3) how many calls the service handled each year since 1 October 2012.","false","Biography information for Baroness Prosser",,"Baroness Prosser","HL4819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439767","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-08","<p>In considering fraud against European own resources, including VAT collection, the European Court recently clarified in the <em>Taricco</em> judgment that Member States are obliged under EU law (Article 325 of the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union) to have in place effective and dissuasive criminal penalties against VAT fraud. The UK applies a full range of penalties to address various behaviours from dishonesty and deliberate inaccuracies through to criminal prosecutions for VAT offences.</p><br />",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2016-01-08T13:58:00.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439767/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439767/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439767/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-22","VAT: Tax Evasion","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of their obligation under EU law to prevent VAT evasion.","false","Biography information for Lord Lucas",,"Lord Lucas","HL4820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439768","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-08","<p>Online marketplaces have no liability for unpaid VAT where the operator merely provides a marketplace for businesses to sell goods. However, HM Revenue and Customs is continuing to work with major online marketplaces to tackle this issue.</p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2016-01-08T13:58:42.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439768/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439768/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439768/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-22","Electronic Commerce: VAT","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the liability of online marketplaces for unpaid VAT where a business trading in that marketplace evades VAT.","false","Biography information for Lord Lucas",,"Lord Lucas","HL4821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439769","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-08","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) has a range of operational activity in place to tackle evasion and to establish evidence of the scale of the problem. HMRC does not routinely carry out test purchases through online platforms.</p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2016-01-08T13:55:22.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439769/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439769/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439769/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-22","Electronic Commerce: VAT","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have conducted any test purchases in online markets to provide evidence of the evasion of VAT.","false","Biography information for Lord Lucas",,"Lord Lucas","HL4822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439770","Department for Education","false","2016-01-08","<p>Research, such as the Early Years Learning and Development Literature Review 2009, and the January 2013 WAVE Trust report on early years, suggests that children need secure attachments with adults in order to feel safe and happy. Good home care can provide this support, which is a real benefit to children as they learn and develop.</p><p>The Department has extensively assessed the impact of formal early education compared to home care, through its longitudinal research programme Effective Pre-School, Primary &amp; Secondary Education Project (EPPSE). EPPSE followed both groups of children through preschool and school ages, examining their cognitive and social behavioural development up to their AS and A Level exam results in 2015. The EPPSE results show that young children benefit from formal childcare, go on to have better GCSE results and, as a result, are more likely to enter A Level exams.</p><p>In recognition of the crucial role that parents and carers play in children’s development, the Early Years Foundation Stage (EYFS) requires childcare settings to form strong partnerships with parents. The EYFS also requires settings to allocate each child a key worker to help ensure that every child’s learning and care is tailored to meet their individual needs.</p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2016-01-08T14:28:17.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439770/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439770/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439770/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-22","Child Rearing","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of studies which conclude that there is a correlation between early direct maternal care and adult stability.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Dundee",,"The Earl of Dundee","HL4823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439771","Department for Education","false","2016-01-08","<p>Research suggests that children need secure attachments with adults in order to feel safe and happy[1]. Good home care can provide this support, which is a real benefit to children as they learn and develop.</p><p>There is also a wide body of evidence, including evidence from abroad, which demonstrates that early education delivered by childcare providers can play an important role in children’s early development and later attainment. For instance, the Effective Pre-school, Primary and Secondary Education (EPPSE 3-16) Project showed that children who had experienced a good home learning environment and attended a good quality childcare setting went on to obtain better grades in English and maths, and to earn more than those who received little or no pre-school experience.</p><p>Additionally, the ongoing Study of Early Education and Development (SEED) shows that the chances of disadvantaged children becoming high achievers by the end of primary school were doubled when they had attended any pre-school, compared to those of disadvantaged children who had not attended pre-school.</p><p>In recognition of the crucial role that parents and carers play in children’s development, the Early Years Foundation Stage (EYFS) requires childcare settings to form strong partnerships with parents. The EYFS also requires settings to allocate each child a key worker to help ensure that every child’s learning and care is tailored to meet their individual needs.</p><p>[1] Early Years Learning and Development Literature Review 2009, and WAVE Trust report ‘Conception to age 2: the age of opportunity’ January 2013.</p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2016-01-08T11:06:12.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439771/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439771/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439771/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-22","Child Rearing","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of studies which show that children benefit most from home care provided by close family members rather than from that available in children's day centres.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Dundee",,"The Earl of Dundee","HL4824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439772","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-08","<p>There are currently no plans to provide at least three years' financial assistance, where such subsidy is independent of paid work, for maternal care in the home.</p>",,"Baroness Altmann",,"2016-01-08T11:06:27.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439772/answer","Biography information for Baroness Altmann","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439772/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439772/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-22","Pregnancy: Health","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to provide at least three years' financial assistance, where such subsidy is independent of paid work, for maternal care in the home.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Dundee",,"The Earl of Dundee","HL4825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439661","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-06","This is ultimately a matter for the Union Government of India and state government of Andhra Pradesh. The UK has worked closely with the Union and state governments in India to strengthen women’s rights and welcomes any new legislation which seeks to further protect women and girls.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-01-06T15:14:16.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439661/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439661/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439661/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-21","India: Dalits","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the decision by the state government of Andhra Pradesh to enable the enforcement of the Andhra Pradesh Devadasis (Prohibition of Dedication) Act 1988 through the Andhra Pradesh Devadasis Prohibition of Dedication Rules 2015, and of the impact of that decision on Dalit women and girls in that state.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL4737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439662","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-06","<p>This is ultimately a matter for the Union Government of India and state governments. Nevertheless, the British Government has worked closely with the Union and state governments in India to strengthen the protection of women’s rights and would welcome any legislative change that provided further protection to women and girls.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-01-06T15:21:12.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439662/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439662/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439662/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-21","India: Dalits","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they plan to make to the state government of Telangana about following the example of the state government of Andhra Pradesh in introducing rules to prevent the sexual exploitation of Dalit women and girls through the Devadasi and Jogini systems of ritualised prostitution.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL4738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439663","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-07","<p>This Government takes flood prevention extremely seriously and we are investing £2.3 billion in flood defences over the next six years, as well as protecting flood maintenance spending in real terms over this Parliament.</p><p>We have put in place strong safeguards to stop inappropriate development in areas at risk of flooding, and are delivering the homes this country needs by taking forward plans to build homes on suitable brownfield land.</p><p>The Environment Agency provides advice on whether or not to grant permission, with latest figures showing 99% of proposed new homes had planning outcomes in line with their advice, but final decisions rest with local authorities.</p><p>The Department does not collect figures for the numbers of homes for which planning permission for building on a flood plain has been granted.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2016-01-07T13:45:36.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439663/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439663/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439663/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-12-21","Floods: Housing","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many homes have been built on flood plains in each of the last five years; and how many homes have been granted planning permission for building on flood plains.","false","Biography information for Baroness Bakewell of Hardington Mandeville",,"Baroness Bakewell of Hardington Mandeville","HL4739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439664","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-06","<p>The British Government is very concerned about the case of Abdullah al-Zaher. We have raised these cases at a senior level in the Government of Saudi Arabia. The UK opposes the death penalty in all circumstances and in every country, especially in cases which do not meet the minimum standards defined by the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights. This includes the execution of a minor and the use of the death penalty for a crime which is not deemed “the most serious”. We take every opportunity to make the Saudi authorities aware of our views.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-01-06T15:22:08.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439664/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439664/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439664/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-21","Adbullah Hasan al-Zaher","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Saudi Arabia in relation to the death sentence imposed on Abdullah ah-Zaher; and whether they will consider taking action in the event of representations on this, and similar cases, going unheeded.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL4740"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439665","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-05","<p>This information is not held in the format requested.</p>",,"Earl Howe","HL4785 ; HL4786 ; HL4787","2016-01-05T16:13:47.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439665/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439665/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-21","Navy: Disciplinary Proceedings","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many complaints have been raised, and disciplinary proceedings brought, annually over the last 20 years involving the interaction between men and women serving on Royal Navy warships and submarines.","false","Biography information for Lord Burnett",,"Lord Burnett","HL4741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439666","Department for International Development","false","2016-01-07","<p>DFID does not have any secondments in place with small business. Its two-way secondment arrangements with the private sector have been with larger firms, including a current inward secondment from Glaxo Smith Kline and a previous outward secondment to John Lewis.</p><br /><p>Aside from secondments, DFID recruits from the private sector, contracts in private sector expertise, benefits from pro bono arrangments with a number of firms, and maintains close partnerships and dialogue with the private sector.</p><br /><p><br></p><br />",,"Baroness Verma",,"2016-01-07T12:43:39.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439666/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439666/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439666/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-12-21","Developing Countries: Small Businesses","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether there are any two-way secondment programmes in place in the Department for International Development to foster a comprehensive understanding of small business development.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hodgson of Abinger",,"Baroness Hodgson of Abinger","HL4742"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439667","Department for International Development","false","2016-01-07","<p>DFID employs cadres of sector-specific technical experts in a range of disciplines in order to provide intellectual and professional rigour to underpin our poverty reduction work. DFID has a cadre of over 80 private sector development advisers who lead our work to support private sector growth, including small business grant funding. Over 80% of private sector development advisers have worked in the private sector, bringing to DFID a first-hand understanding of business development.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2016-01-07T12:44:09.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439667/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439667/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439667/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-12-21","Developing Countries: Small Businesses","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether any of those staff at the Department for International Development involved in small business grant funding have hands-on experience of business development.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hodgson of Abinger",,"Baroness Hodgson of Abinger","HL4743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439668","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-06","Somalia’s Aid Coordination Unit (ACU), supported by the World Bank and UN Development Programme, has reported that donors are meeting and sometimes exceeding their pledges. The 2013 pledge to implement the New Deal was 2.4 billion US dollars. ACU estimate that donors spent 3.2 billion US dollars across 2014 and 2015, exceeding the pledge by 33 per cent. According to ACU, donors have consistently delivered 1 billion US dollars annually in Overseas Development Assistance, accompanied by significant resources for peacekeeping and military aid.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-01-06T15:23:40.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439668/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439668/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439668/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-21","Somalia: International Assistance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the percentage of the funds pledged by all nations through the 2013 Somali Compact that has been spent.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hodgson of Abinger",,"Baroness Hodgson of Abinger","HL4744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439669","Department of Health","false","2016-01-06","<p>Health Education England (HEE) has been established to ensure the National Health Service has access to the right numbers of staff, at the right time and with the right skills. In doing so, HEE works with key external stakeholders to develop its National Workforce Plan for England which sets out the number of training places it will commission in the year ahead.</p><br /><p>HEE will formally publish the 2016-17 National Workforce Plan for England in January 2016. In both 2014/15 and 2015/16, HEE commissioned 362 training places in Podiatry and Chiropody across England, maintaining the current supply.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-01-06T15:03:13.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439669/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439669/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439669/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-21","Podiatry: Training","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with Health Education England to ensure that the number of chiropody and podiatry student commissions for 2016–17 is sufficient to meet demand.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL4745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439670","Department of Health","false","2016-01-06","<p>We have made no such assessment.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-01-06T15:04:33.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439670/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439670/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439670/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-21","Dermatology: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the number of patients who are unable to access dermatology specials when they need them.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL4746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439671","Department of Health","false","2016-01-06","<p>The Drug Tariff sets out what National Health Service dispensing contractors will be paid for the products supplied as part of providing pharmaceutical services and the fees for providing those services in primary care.</p><br /><p>The current arrangements in the Drug Tariff for paying for specials, including dermatological specials, were introduced in 2011. It is recognised that there can be variations in the price of some specials, which is why we are considering further possible improvements in the arrangements that govern the price the NHS pays. These include expanding the number of products covered by these arrangements and improving the data used to set the prices.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL4748 ; HL4750","2016-01-06T15:05:52.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439671/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439671/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439671/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-21","Dermatology: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what consideration they have given to reviewing the process for the price setting of dermatology specials, and according to what timeframe.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL4747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439672","Department of Health","false","2016-01-06","<p>The Drug Tariff sets out what National Health Service dispensing contractors will be paid for the products supplied as part of providing pharmaceutical services and the fees for providing those services in primary care.</p><br /><p>The current arrangements in the Drug Tariff for paying for specials, including dermatological specials, were introduced in 2011. It is recognised that there can be variations in the price of some specials, which is why we are considering further possible improvements in the arrangements that govern the price the NHS pays. These include expanding the number of products covered by these arrangements and improving the data used to set the prices.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL4747 ; HL4750","2016-01-06T15:05:52.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439672/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439672/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439672/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-21","Dermatology: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the alternative processes for the NHS tariff price setting of dermatology specials, including the addition of NHS manufacturers’ costings in the tariff setting process.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL4748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439673","Department of Health","false","2016-01-06","<p>Members of the Association of Pharmaceutical Specials Manufacturers do not provide the Department with reference price data for their products. Individual manufacturers provide data on their sales volumes and selling prices to the Department under a memorandum of understanding between manufacturers and the Department. This data is then used to set a reimbursement price which reflects the price at which community pharmacies purchased these products in the quarter before.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-01-06T15:07:09.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439673/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439673/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439673/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-21","NHS: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their assessment of the risk of a conflict of interest when members of the Association of Pharmaceutical Specials Manufacturers both provide the reference prices from which to set the NHS tariff prices for specials in the primary care sector and supply those specials to community pharmacists.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL4749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439674","Department of Health","false","2016-01-06","<p>The Drug Tariff sets out what National Health Service dispensing contractors will be paid for the products supplied as part of providing pharmaceutical services and the fees for providing those services in primary care.</p><br /><p>The current arrangements in the Drug Tariff for paying for specials, including dermatological specials, were introduced in 2011. It is recognised that there can be variations in the price of some specials, which is why we are considering further possible improvements in the arrangements that govern the price the NHS pays. These include expanding the number of products covered by these arrangements and improving the data used to set the prices.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL4747 ; HL4748","2016-01-06T15:05:52.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439674/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439674/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439674/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-21","NHS: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the level of mark-ups on dermatology specials, what consideration they have given to reforming the process by which English NHS tariff prices are set.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL4750"
